### Initiative #14 — Didasko (Academic)
**Crown:** Sal Khan — Chancellor
**Crown letter file:** `CROWN_LETTER_SAL_KHAN_V02.md` (LOCKED)
**Category:** Education / K-12 / Lifelong Learning
**Description (from 01_SAL_KHAN_LETTER.md verbatim):**
> "Didasko is the education initiative within Liana Banyan — a cooperative commerce platform where
> creators keep 83.3% of everything they earn. Didasko is built on the same principle [as Khan
> Academy]: education should be accessible to everyone."
**How Didasko Works:** Educators on the platform create courses, curricula, tutoring sessions.
Students access through cooperative membership. Educators keep 83.3%. Crown Council guidance from
Chancellor. Sal Khan letter references "cooperative education" as both access AND economic sustainability.
**Status:** Crown letter written (LOCKED)

